{"hitCount": 1, "request": {"cursorMark": "*", "pageSize": 1, "queryString": "DOI:\"10.1016/j.jconrel.2013.11.002\"", "resultType": "core", "sort": "", "synonym": false}, "resultList": {"result": [{"abstractText": "Stimulated Raman scattering microscopy was used to assess the permeation of topically applied drugs and formulation excipients into porcine skin. This chemically selective technique generates high-resolution 3D images, from which semi-quantitative information may be elucidated. Ibuprofen, applied as a close-to-saturated solution in propylene glycol, was directly observed to crystallise in/on the skin, as the co-solvent permeated more rapidly, resulting in precipitation of the drug. Coherent Raman scattering microscopy is also an excellent tool, in conjunction with more conventional confocal fluorescence microscopy, with which to image micro/nanoparticle-based formulations. Specifically, the uptake of particles into thermal ablation transport pathways in the skin has been examined.", "affiliation": "Department of Pharmacy & Pharmacology, University of Bath, BathBA2 7AY, UK.", "authMan": "N", "authorIdList": {"authorId": [{"type": "ORCID", "value": "0000-0001-6208-7840"}, {"type": "ORCID", "value": "0000-0001-7773-0966"}, {"type": "ORCID", "value": "0000-0002-3802-9154"}, {"type": "ORCID", "value": "0000-0003-3227-9862"}, {"type": "ORCID", "value": "0000-0003-4983-5722"}]}, "authorList": {"author": [{"authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": [{"affiliation": "Department of Pharmacy & Pharmacology, University of Bath, BathBA2 7AY, UK."}]}, "authorId": {"type": "ORCID", "value": "0000-0001-7773-0966"}, "firstName": "Natalie A", "fullName": "Belsey NA", "initials": "NA", "lastName": "Belsey"}, {"authorAffiliationDetailsList": {"authorAffiliation": [{"affiliation": "Department of Physics, University of Exeter, ExeterEX4 4QL, UK."}]}, "authorId": {"type": "ORCID", "value": "0000-0002-3802-9154"}, "firstName": "Natalie L", "fullName": "Garrett NL", "i